    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-03-04T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-03-04T06:00:00-05:00" n="106"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d106">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.60F31/62: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wright</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Praha</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-04T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 4, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received March 4—10:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12. Your instructions numbers 20, January 11 and 29, February 14.<note n="6"
                        xml:id="d106fn6">Neither printed.</note> The press now gives prominence to
                    the report that you intend to make public a list of those nations “which will
                    not relinquish certain import restrictions which the United States considers
                    unjustified.” Foreign Office official has intimated the concern of this
                    Government lest it be included therein and inquires whether it may be informed
                    as to specific instances if any. In view of results of representations, reported
                    in my telegram 11, March 4, 11 a.m.,<note n="7" xml:id="d106fn7">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_170">p. 170</ref>.</note> I
                    may be able to utilize <pb facs="0216" n="140" xml:id="pg_140"/> to advantage
                    information of this nature if such be your intention and have already mentioned
                    difficulties with automobiles, lard, and prunes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wright</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
